comments.body:
@ShivanKaul - discussing at DNSOP is also a reasonable option.

At the end of the day, I think we'll need to reconcile this draft with the relevant CAB forum rules, as those rules are how the WebPKI works.

So if there is a compelling reason against the underscore rule for the owner name, we'll need to state what that is and then try to persuade the CAB forum. If there isn't or if there is a compelling reason to have the rule (to avoid collisions with legitimate hostnames), then I think we should add something like this PR.
